    "details": "A vulnerability, which was classified as problematic, was found in HDF5 up to 1.14.6. This affects the function `H5HL__fl_deserialize` of the file `src/H5HLcache.c`. The manipulation of the argument `free_block` leads to heap-based buffer overflow. It is possible to launch the attack on the local host. The exploit has been disclosed to the public and may be used.",
